Input data

#load reads:
#If tpms:
geneExp <- read.table("/sc/orga/projects/pd-omics/data/amp-pd/evan/amp-pd_baseline_counts.txt", header = TRUE, row.names = 1, check.names = F)

info1 <- read.csv("/sc/orga/projects/pd-omics/data/amp-pd/evan/amp-pd_metadata.csv", header = TRUE, row.names = 1)
geneExp = geneExp[rownames(info1)]
norm = calcNormFactors(geneExp, method = "TMM")
x <- DGEList(counts=geneExp, samples=info1, norm.factors = norm)
v = voom(x)
mynd_voom = v$E

#After sure that they are similar, force them.
identical(colnames(mynd_voom), rownames(info1))

Violin Plot

#removed all low expressed genes
cpm = cpm(geneExp)
keep.exp = rowSums(cpm > 1) >= 0.3*ncol(geneExp)
ge = mynd_voom[keep.exp,]
#Variables to run Variance Partition with selected variables. Remember (1|..) for factors!
form <- ~(1|status) + age_at_baseline + (1|sex) + (1|Plate) + (1|Box) + (1|race) +  PCT_RIBOSOMAL_BASES + RIN_Value + PCT_INTERGENIC_BASES + PCT_USABLE_BASES + X_260_230_Ratio

#The variance partiation run:
varPart <- fitExtractVarPartModel( ge, form, info1 )
vp <- sortCols ( varPart )
plotVarPart ( vp )
